    "body": "### Problem\n\n`vim.fs.find` and `vim.fs.dir` doesn't support `X:/` path on windows.\r\nAfter some debug, found that `vim.fs.dir` can not list files under path `X:`, which is resulted from that `vim.fs.normalize` will convert `X:/` into `X:`. Is it a bug?\r\n(Currently I have to change `X:/` into `X:/.` before passed into `vim.fs.find` to work around)\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n```lua\r\nfor name, type in vim.fs.dir(\"E:/\") do\r\n    print(name, type) -- Got wrong files\r\nend\r\nfor name, type in vim.fs.dir(\"E:/.\") do\r\n    print(name, type) -- Got correct files\r\nend\r\n```\r\n\n\n### Expected behavior\n\n`vim.fs.find` and `vim.fs.dir` work correctly for `X:/` path on windows.\n\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.9\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nwindows 11\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nxterm\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm\n\n### Installation\n\nnvim.exe",
